The paper presents methods for k-means clustering on a stream, which involves processing large amounts of data in a continuous and online manner. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on providing fast responses to clustering queries, which involves optimizing the performance of the algorithms used. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category, which deals with the development of algorithms for learning from data. The paper also involves the use of coresets, which are summaries of data that can be used to speed up computations, suggesting that it may belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category, which deals with the storage and retrieval of large amounts of data. Finally, the paper involves the use of theoretical results and experiments to demonstrate the correctness and efficiency of the algorithms used, suggesting that it may also belong to the cs.DM (Data Mining) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories, which deal with the development of algorithms for analyzing and making predictions from data.
